<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-59-0704 </DOCNO><TEXT>The principles governing solar energy conversion, and the kind of applicationsin which solar collectors can be used, are described: heat exchangers,possibility to drive heat engines, domestic water heating, refrigeration,and upgrading heat (e.g. by reversed absorption). Some remarks on theupper limits to the conversion of solar energy conclude this paper. 4figs., 5 refs., 1 tab.</TEXT></DOC>